<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Group_mim  Type: groupable_item 
   <express_ref linkend="group:mim:Group_mim.groupable_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Group_mim.groupable_item">
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Group_mim.groupable_item.wr:WR1">
A groupable item shall not be a <b>group</b> or any subtype of <b>group</b>.
<note>Group nesting can be represented using <b>group_relationship</b>.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Group_mim  Entity: applied_group_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Group_mim.applied_group_assignment">
An <b>applied_group_assignment</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.group_assignment"/> that associates a <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group"/> with one or more <b>groupable_item</b> instances.
<p>The considered group is specified with the inherited attribute assigned_group. The meaning of the association is specified with the inherited attribute role.</p>
<p>In order to represent the inclusion of elements in a group, the value 'group membership' shall be used for that role.</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Group_mim  Entity: applied_group_assignment  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Group_mim.applied_group_assignment.items">
the set of one or more instances that are associated with the group referred to by the inherited attribute <b>assigned_group</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
